Mind we have never played enough to have uber characters of lvl55+, but we have done many things to try and keep the game interesting, FirionaVie being the latest.<br>
I believe the game basically comes down to three things:<br>
LOOT, LEVEL and LOOKS ( I call it L-cube ). Many of us who fled blue servers to play on FV did so to a large extent as a negative reaction to L-cube and all it fosters on other EQ servers.<br>
Changes are needed, but not to the rules that make this server unique. FV seems to have many genuinely new players to EQ since Christmas...anyone else interested in helping to shape them up while playing their own characters also? A college, as it were?<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=nalir>Nalir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/20/02 9:24:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1151.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The server is dying... slowly but surely</span><hr size=1> I almost totally left my old server (Morell Thule) in the past for Sullon Zek. Friends left with me, we had grand plans...but over time, only I remained in Sullon Zek. The others couldn't stand/survive the harsh environment there.<br>
<br>
SZ is in one option a bit like FV: Constantly declining population and people leaving because of the bad points. I both love playing on SZ and FV because of the good parts of it.<br>
<br>
SZ in one way has a terribly immature population. Many griefers, 'dewds' and....plain idiots. Yet they have become part of the game. The guild I joined there used to have over 60 members, and was an evil RP-oriented guild. Yet we are about to disband since only three members are still around regularly.<br>
<br>
The good parts about SZ though is that it is always challenging. I normally hunt in enemy territory, which means I get ambushed at the worst moments, and have to deal with it instantly, I myself get to ambush enemies who most of the time have better odds, yet it is never boring there. The harsh environment of SZ is something I strangely prefer over a regular blue server: log in, seek group, get exp, get loot, log out.<br>
<br>
FV also has bad points everyone who comes here will notice: TLC (I like the TLC though), oppresive silence (even if there are 30 people in an area it's dead quiet, we don't have to listen to the ooc crap from blue servers, but total silence is annoying as well), one character and communication is hard with the language system.<br>
<br>
But when you look at the good parts of FV...this is the only server where I won't be looked strange at for being my character, being in-character, the only server where almost everyone I meet is a character, and not just a_level_x_class. The reason I started EQ years ago was because I wanted to play a mmoRPg...and FV finally made that possible (though Morell Thule also already had a very active roleplay community, so I had it better there then I would have on many other servers, like Veeshan and Prexus where I played before MT).<br>
<br>
<br>
Yours truly,<br>
